summarise_order <- function(df){
  df2 <- df[!is.na(df$OrderLevel), ]
  order_bp <- tapply(df2$length, df2$OrderLevel, sum)
  order_copies <- tapply(df2$length, df2$OrderLevel, length)
  total_bp <- sum(order_bp)
  
  data.frame(
    Order = names(order_bp),
    te_bp = as.numeric(order_bp),
    copies = as.numeric(order_copies),
    frac_TE = (as.numeric(order_bp)/total_bp)*100
  )
}

jap_ord <- summarise_order(jap)
bra_ord <- summarise_order(bra)

head(jap_ord)
head(bra_ord)
comp_ord <- merge(
  jap_ord, bra_ord,
  by="Order", all=TRUE,
  suffixes=c("_jap","_bra")
)

comp_ord[is.na(comp_ord)] <- 0
comp_ord$total_bp <- comp_ord$te_bp_jap + comp_ord$te_bp_bra
comp_ord <- comp_ord[order(-comp_ord$total_bp), ]

summarise_family <- function(df){
  df2 <- df[!is.na(df$FamilyLevel), ]
  fam_bp <- tapply(df2$length, df2$FamilyLevel, sum)
  fam_copies <- tapply(df2$length, df2$FamilyLevel, length)
  total_bp <- sum(fam_bp)
  
  data.frame(
    Family   = names(fam_bp),
    te_bp    = as.numeric(fam_bp),
    copies   = as.numeric(fam_copies),
    frac_TE  = (as.numeric(fam_bp)/total_bp)*100,
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
  )
}

jap_fam <- summarise_family(jap)
bra_fam <- summarise_family(bra)

fam_comp <- merge(
  jap_fam, bra_fam,
  by = "Family",
  all = TRUE,
  suffixes = c("_jap", "_bra")
)

fam_comp[is.na(fam_comp)] <- 0
fam_comp$total_bp <- fam_comp$te_bp_jap + fam_comp$te_bp_bra
fam_comp <- fam_comp[order(-fam_comp$total_bp), ]

get_genome_size <- function(fasta_path) {
  con <- file(fasta_path, "r")
  on.exit(close(con))
  
  total_bp <- 0L
  
  repeat {
    line <- readLines(con, n = 1)
    if (length(line) == 0) break  # end of file
    
    if (substr(line, 1, 1) == ">") {
      # header line, skip
      next
    } else {
      # sequence line
      total_bp <- total_bp + nchar(line)
    }
  }
  
  return(total_bp)
}

size_bra <- get_genome_size("Oryza_brachyantha.Oryza_brachyantha.v1.4b.dna.toplevel.fa")

# function to get genome info
get_chrom_lengths <- function(fasta_path) {
  lines <- readLines(fasta_path)
  headers <- grep("^>", lines)
  result <- data.frame(chr = character(), length = numeric())

  for (i in seq_along(headers)) {
    header <- lines[headers[i]]
    chr_name <- gsub("^>|\\s.*$", "", header)
    start <- headers[i] + 1
    end <- ifelse(i == length(headers), length(lines), headers[i+1] - 1)
    seq_len <- sum(nchar(lines[start:end]))
    result <- rbind(result, data.frame(chr = chr_name, length = seq_len))
  }
  result
}

# Get chromosome info

bra_chroms <- get_chrom_lengths("Oryza_brachyantha.Oryza_brachyantha.v1.4b.dna.toplevel.fa")

### 3) Make 1 Mb windows
make_windows <- function(chroms, window = 1e6) {
  out <- list()
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(chroms))) {
    chr <- chroms$chr[i]
    len <- chroms$length[i]
    starts <- seq(1, len, by = window)
    ends <- pmin(starts + window - 1, len)
    out[[i]] <- data.frame(
      chr = chr,
      start = starts,
      end = ends,
      window_id = seq_along(starts)
    )
  }
  do.call(rbind, out)
}

jap_win <- make_windows(jap_chroms)
bra_win <- make_windows(bra_chroms)

### 4) Compute TE density per window
compute_density <- function(te_df, window_df) {
  out <- window_df
  out$te_bp <- 0
  
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(out))) {
    wchr <- out$chr[i]
    wstart <- out$start[i]
    wend <- out$end[i]

    sub <- te_df[te_df$seqid == wchr &
                   te_df$end >= wstart &
                   te_df$start <= wend, ]

    if (nrow(sub) > 0) {
      bp <- sum(pmax(0, pmin(sub$end, wend) - pmax(sub$start, wstart) + 1))
      out$te_bp[i] <- bp
    }
  }

  out$te_density <- out$te_bp / (out$end - out$start + 1)
  out
}

jap_density <- compute_density(jap, jap_win)
bra_density <- compute_density(bra, bra_win)

collapse_TE_insertions <- function(df, gap = 50) {
  # keep only valid numeric coordinates
  df <- df[!is.na(df$start) & !is.na(df$end), ]
  df <- df[df$end >= df$start, ]
  
  # sort by chromosome and start
  df <- df[order(df$seqid, df$start), ]
  
  out <- list()
  out_i <- 1L
  
  for (chr in unique(df$seqid)) {
    sub <- df[df$seqid == chr, ]
    if (nrow(sub) == 0) next
    
    cs <- sub$start[1]
    ce <- sub$end[1]
    
    if (is.na(cs) || is.na(ce)) next  # skip bad first row just in case
    
    if (nrow(sub) == 1) {
      out[[out_i]] <- data.frame(
        seqid = chr,
        start = cs,
        end   = ce,
        length = ce - cs + 1L
      )
      out_i <- out_i + 1L
      next
    }
    
    for (i in 2:nrow(sub)) {
      st <- sub$start[i]
      en <- sub$end[i]
      
      # if current row is bad, skip it
      if (is.na(st) || is.na(en)) next
      
      # if overlap or small gap, extend current insertion
      if (st <= ce + gap) {
        ce <- max(ce, en)
      } else {
        # close previous insertion
        out[[out_i]] <- data.frame(
          seqid = chr,
          start = cs,
          end   = ce,
          length = ce - cs + 1L
        )
        out_i <- out_i + 1L
        
        # start new insertion
        cs <- st
        ce <- en
      }
    }
    
    # add last insertion for this chromosome
    out[[out_i]] <- data.frame(
      seqid = chr,
      start = cs,
      end   = ce,
      length = ce - cs + 1L
    )
    out_i <- out_i + 1L
  }
  
  do.call(rbind, out)
}


jap_insertions <- collapse_TE_insertions(jap, gap = 50)
bra_insertions <- collapse_TE_insertions(bra, gap = 50)

nearest_gene_distance <- function(insertions, genes) {
  res_list <- list()
  common_chr <- intersect(unique(insertions$seqid), unique(genes$seqid))
  
  for (chr in common_chr) {
    ins <- insertions[insertions$seqid == chr, ]
    gen <- genes[genes$seqid == chr, ]
    
    if (nrow(ins) == 0 || nrow(gen) == 0) next
    
    # gene midpoints sorted
    gen_mid <- (gen$start + gen$end) / 2
    o <- order(gen_mid)
    gen_mid <- gen_mid[o]
    
    # TE midpoints
    te_mid <- (ins$start + ins$end) / 2
    
    # interval indices
    idx <- findInterval(te_mid, gen_mid)
    
    # candidate distances: left and right neighbor
    left  <- pmax(idx, 1)
    right <- pmin(idx + 1, length(gen_mid))
    
    d_left  <- abs(te_mid - gen_mid[left])
    d_right <- abs(te_mid - gen_mid[right])
    
    dist <- pmin(d_left, d_right)
    
    ins$dist_to_gene <- dist
    res_list[[length(res_list) + 1]] <- ins
  }
  
  do.call(rbind, res_list)
}

gene_min_TE_dist <- function(insertions, genes) {
  res_list <- list()
  
  common_chr <- intersect(unique(insertions$seqid), unique(genes$seqid))
  
  for (chr in common_chr) {
    ins <- insertions[insertions$seqid == chr, ]
    gen <- genes[genes$seqid == chr, ]
    
    if (nrow(ins) == 0 || nrow(gen) == 0) next
    
    # TE midpoints
    te_mid <- (ins$start + ins$end) / 2
    
    # Gene midpoints
    gmid <- (gen$start + gen$end) / 2
    
    # sort TE midpoints for faster nearest search
    o <- order(te_mid)
    te_mid_sorted <- te_mid[o]
    
    # for each gene, find nearest TE using findInterval
    idx <- findInterval(gmid, te_mid_sorted)
    
    left  <- pmax(idx, 1)
    right <- pmin(idx + 1, length(te_mid_sorted))
    
    d_left  <- abs(gmid - te_mid_sorted[left])
    d_right <- abs(gmid - te_mid_sorted[right])
    
    min_dist <- pmin(d_left, d_right)
    
    tmp <- data.frame(
      gene_id = gen$gene_id,
      min_dist = min_dist,
      stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    )
    res_list[[length(res_list) + 1]] <- tmp
  }
  
  do.call(rbind, res_list)
}

## =========================================================
## 4. TE density along chromosomes (all TEs, 1 Mb windows)
## =========================================================

make_windows_from_TE <- function(te_df, window = 1e6) {
  chrom_lengths <- te_df %>%
    group_by(seqid) %>%
    summarise(chr_len = max(end), .groups = "drop")
  
  win_list <- list()
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(chrom_lengths))) {
    chr   <- chrom_lengths$seqid[i]
    len   <- chrom_lengths$chr_len[i]
    
    starts <- seq(1, len, by = window)
    ends   <- pmin(starts + window - 1, len)
    
    win_list[[i]] <- data.frame(
      seqid = chr,
      ws    = starts,
      we    = ends,
      mid   = (starts + ends) / 2,
      stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    )
  }
  bind_rows(win_list)
}

compute_density <- function(te_df, windows_df) {
  res <- windows_df
  res$te_bp <- 0
  
  if (!"length" %in% colnames(te_df)) {
    te_df$length <- te_df$end - te_df$start + 1
  }
  
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(res))) {
    chr <- res$seqid[i]
    ws  <- res$ws[i]
    we  <- res$we[i]
    
    sub <- te_df %>%
      filter(seqid == chr,
             end   >= ws,
             start <= we)
    
    if (nrow(sub) > 0) {
      ov <- pmax(0, pmin(sub$end, we) - pmax(sub$start, ws) + 1)
      res$te_bp[i] <- sum(ov)
    }
  }
  
  res$window_len <- res$we - res$ws + 1
  res$density    <- res$te_bp / res$window_len
  res
}

## japonica

## 5. TEgene proximity categories (Fig. 2C-style)
## =========================================================
## Assumes you have data frames:
##   jap_gene_dist, bra_gene_dist
## each with at least:
##   dist_to_gene  (numeric, absolute distance in bp)
## If your object/column names differ, change them here.

## ---- Example: create a fake dist_to_gene from your previous object ----
## jap_gene_dist <- jap_TEdist   # if that's what you called it
## bra_gene_dist <- bra_TEdist

## Define categories based on distance (approximate version of Fig. 2C)

categorise_dist <- function(d) {
  case_when(
    d == 0                       ~ "genic",
    d  > 0        & d <=  1000   ~ "prox_<=1kb",
    d  > 1000     & d <=  3000   ~ "prox_1-3kb",
    d  > 3000     & d <= 10000   ~ "prox_3-10kb",
    d  > 10000                  ~ "distal_>10kb",
    TRUE                        ~ "unknown"
  )
}
